**Sierra Leone is a country located in West Africa, with a land area of approximately 71,740 square kilometers. The country has a triangular shape, with a coastline along the Atlantic Ocean to the west, and borders with Guinea to the north and east, and Liberia to the south. The capital city, Freetown, is located on the western coast of the country, and is the largest city in Sierra Leone. Other prominent cities and towns in Sierra Leone include Bo, Kenema, Makeni, Koidu, Port Loko, Kabala, and Bonthe. Sierra Leone has several prominent rivers, including the Rokel River, Little Scarcies River, Great Scarcies River, and the Sewa River. These rivers are important for transportation, agriculture, and fishing. The Rokel River is the largest river in Sierra Leone, and is approximately 515 kilometers long. Sierra Leone has a diverse landscape, with savannah grasslands in the east, dense forests in the south and west, and mountainous regions in the central part of the country. The highest point in Sierra Leone is Mount Bintumani, which is approximately 1,945 meters tall. Some of the prominent places in Sierra Leone include the Tacugama Chimpanzee Sanctuary, Banana Islands, Outamba-Kilimi National Park, Bunce Island, and Tiwai Island Wildlife Sanctuary. These places are important for tourism, conservation, and research purposes. The cordinates represent the northernmost and southernmost points of the country's border with Guinea, and the westernmost and easternmost points of the country's border with Liberia. The capital city, Freetown, is located at approximately 8.4650° N, 13.2316° W. The coordinates for other prominent cities and towns in Sierra Leone are: Bo: 7.9643° N, 11.7380° W Kenema: 7.8769° N, 11.1877° W Makeni: 8.8818° N, 12.0512° W Koidu: 8.4244° N, 10.5555° W [...]** - <@934739084503556106> (fast)
